Time Limit: 0.5 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description
Given N numbers. Count how many of these values are even, odd, positive, and negative.

Input Format
First line contains one number N, number of values.

Second line contains N numbers where ith number from start is called Xi.

Output Format
Print four lines with the following format:

First Line: "Even: X"

where X is the number of even numbers in the given input.

Second Line: "Odd: X"

where X is the number of odd numbers in the given input.

Third Line: "Positive: X"

where X is the number of positive numbers in the given input.

Fourth Line: "Negative: X"

where X is the number of negative numbers in the given input.

Constraints
1 ≤ N ≤ 10³
−10⁵ ≤ Xi ≤ 10⁵

Sample Input 1
5
-5 0 -3 -4 12

Sample Output 1
Even: 3
Odd: 2
Positive: 1
Negative: 3

Note
Explanation of Sample Input

Given the input array:
[0, -5, -3, -4, 12]

Even Numbers:
0, -4, 12

Odd Numbers:
-5, -3

Positive Numbers:
12

Negative Numbers:
-5, -3, -4

So the output would be:

Even - 3
Odd - 2
Positive - 1
Negative - 3


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);cout.tie(0);

int n;
cin>>n;
vector<int>v(n);
int eve = 0;
int odd = 0;
int pos = 0;
int neg = 0;
for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
{
   cin>>v[i];
   
}

for(int i = 0; i < n;i++)
{
    if(v[i] % 2 == 0)
   {
      eve++;
   }
   if(v[i] % 2 != 0){
      odd++;
   }
   if(v[i] < 0){
      neg++;
   }
   if(v[i] > 0){
      pos++;
   }
}
cout<<"Even: "<<eve<<endl;
cout<<"Odd: "<<odd<<endl;
cout<<"Positive: "<<pos<<endl;
cout<<"Negative: "<<neg<<endl;
}
